Lines and paths stroked using the BasicStroke object may be "normalized" to provide consistent rendering of the outlines when positioned at various points on the drawable and whether drawn with aliased or antialiased rendering. This normalization process is controlled by the KEY_STROKE_CONTROL hint. The exact normalization algorithm is not specified, but the goals of this normalization are to ensure that lines are rendered with consistent visual appearance regardless of how they fall on the pixel grid and to promote more solid horizontal and vertical lines in antialiased mode so that they resemble their non-antialiased counterparts more closely. A typical normalization step might promote antialiased line endpoints to pixel centers to reduce the amount of blending or adjust the subpixel positioning of non-antialiased lines so that the floating point line widths round to even or odd pixel counts with equal likelihood. This process can move endpoints by up to half a pixel (usually towards positive infinity along both axes) to promote these consistent results.

Such processing is typically initiated by subinterface methods such as SourceDataLine.write and TargetDataLine.read.

trans-unit.source: Locale sensitive factory methods and methods for name retrieval in the java.text and java.util packages invoke service provider methods when needed to support the requested locale. The methods first check whether the Java runtime environment itself supports the requested locale, and use its support if available. Otherwise, they call the isSupportedLocale methods of installed providers for the appropriate interface to find one that supports the requested locale. If such a provider is found, its other methods are called to obtain the requested object or name. When checking whether a locale is supported, the locale's extensions are ignored by default. (If locale's extensions should also be checked, the isSupportedLocale method must be overridden.) If neither the Java runtime environment itself nor an installed provider supports the requested locale, the methods go through a list of candidate locales and repeat the availability check for each until a match is found. The algorithm used for creating a list of candidate locales is same as the one used by ResourceBundle by default (see getCandidateLocales for the details). Even if a locale is resolved from the candidate list, methods that return requested objects or names are invoked with the original requested locale including Locale extensions. The Java runtime environment must support the root locale for all locale sensitive services in order to guarantee that this process terminates.

Los métodos primero verifican si el propio entorno de ejecución de Java es compatible con la configuración regional solicitada y utilizan su soporte si está disponible. De lo contrario, llaman a los métodos isSupportedLocale de los proveedores instalados para que la interfaz adecuada encuentre una que admita la configuración regional solicitada. Si se encuentra dicho proveedor, se invoca a sus otros métodos para obtener el objeto o nombre solicitado. Al comprobar si una configuración regional es compatible, las extensiones de la configuración regional se ignoran de forma predeterminada. (Si también se deben isSupportedLocale las extensiones de la configuración regional, isSupportedLocaleEl método debe anularse.) Si ni el entorno de ejecución de Java ni un proveedor instalado admiten la configuración regional solicitada, los métodos pasan por una lista de configuraciones regionales candidatas y repiten la verificación de disponibilidad para cada una hasta que se encuentra una coincidencia. El algoritmo utilizado para crear una lista de locales candidatos es el mismo que el utilizado por ResourceBundle de forma predeterminada (consulte getCandidateLocales para obtener más detalles). Incluso si una configuración regional se resuelve de la lista de candidatos, los métodos que devuelven los objetos o nombres solicitados se invocan con la configuración Locale solicitada original, incluidas las extensiones de configuración regional . El entorno de ejecución de Java debe admitir el entorno local raíz para todos los servicios sensibles al entorno local para garantizar que este proceso finalice.

trans-unit.source: LogManager properties are updated with the resulting value in the resulting configuration.
LogRecord maintains timestamps with nanosecond resolution, using Instant values.
LogRecord maintains timestamps with nanosecond resolution, using Instant values. For this reason, setInstant() should be used in preference to setMillis().
LogRecord objects are used to pass logging requests between the logging framework and individual log Handlers.
trans-unit.target: Los objetos LogRecord se utilizan para pasar las solicitudes de registro entre el marco de registro y los Manejadores de registro individuales.

trans-unit.source: Logger objects may be obtained by calls on one of the getLogger factory methods. These will either create a new Logger or return a suitable existing Logger. It is important to note that the Logger returned by one of the getLogger factory methods may be garbage collected at any time if a strong reference to the Logger is not kept.
trans-unit.target: Los objetos de registrador se pueden obtener mediante llamadas a uno de los métodos de fábrica de getLogger. Estos crearán un nuevo registrador o devolverán un registrador existente adecuado. Es importante tener en cuenta que el registrador devuelto por uno de los métodos de fábrica de getLogger puede ser recolectado como basura en cualquier momento si no se mantiene una fuerte referencia al registrador.

trans-unit.source: Loggers are organized into a naming hierarchy based on their dot separated names. Thus "a.b.c" is a child of "a.b", but "a.b1" and a.b2" are peers.
trans-unit.target: Los registradores se organizan en una jerarquía de nombres basada en sus nombres separados por puntos.Así,"a.b.c" es hijo de "a.b",pero "a.b1" y "a.b2" son iguales.

trans-unit.source: Logging messages will be forwarded to registered Handler objects, which can forward the messages to a variety of destinations, including consoles, files, OS logs, etc.
trans-unit.target: Los mensajes de registro serán reenviados a los objetos Manejador registrados,que pueden reenviar los mensajes a una variedad de destinos,incluyendo consolas,archivos,registros del sistema operativo,etc.

trans-unit.source: Logging out a Subject involves only one phase. The LoginContext invokes the LoginModule's logout method. The logout method for the LoginModule then performs the logout procedures, such as removing Principals or Credentials from the Subject or logging session information.
trans-unit.target: Cerrar la sesión de un Subject implica solo una fase. El LoginContext invoca del LoginModule logout método. El método de logout para el LoginModule inicio de sesión luego realiza los procedimientos de cierre de sesión, como eliminar los principales o credenciales del Subject o registrar la información de la sesión.
